{"questionId":"32048469","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>98</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>)</mo></math> represents a point at the top of the glass.</p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> be the region enclosed by the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>, the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis and the line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Jules finds the capacity by rotating the region, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>,&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>360</mn><mo>°</mo></math> about the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the capacity of the glass that Jules obtains.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognizing need to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>∫</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></math> <em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>781</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msubsup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></math> <em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award <strong><em>A1</em></strong> for correct limits and squaring <strong>their</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>, seen anywhere.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempt to make <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> the subject. <em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)<br></strong></em><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi></math></p>\n<p>attempt to remove <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi></math> by using exponent base <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>. <em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><strong>(M1)<br></strong></em><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup></math><br><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup></math> <em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)<br><br></strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>631</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>631</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>071</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math> <em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32048469","referenceCode":"24N.1.AHL.TZ0.16b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate the capacity of the glass that Jules obtains.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber"